==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Pronunciation===
* (US) {{IPA|/ˈhækəl/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#one of the peculiar, long, narrow [[feather]]s on the [[neck]] of [[fowl]]s, most noticeable on the cock.
#a [[feather]] [[plume]] on some [[soldier]]'s uniforms.
#[[hair]] on the [[nape]] of the neck.
#*When the dog got angry his '''hackles''' rose and he growled.

===Adjective===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#Descriptive of the feathers of a fowl.
#The '''hackle''' feathers of the cock were long and golden.

====Usage note====
Hackles as a noun are usually spoken of in the plural. Hackle as an adjective is usually spoken of in the singular.

